<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>“The operation took place on Tuesday morning at the corner of Seotshwareng and Barkly roads near Galeshewe,” said Tawana.“We also checked, bakkies, sedans and SUVs. The operation lasted for two hours.“During this period, more than 20 vehicles transporting pupils and staff were stopped to determine compliance with transport regulations.”Twana added that fines to the value of R11 000 were issued for offences which included driving violations, public transport and those relating to roadworthiness.“Taxis and minibuses certified to carry between seven to 16 passengers were overloaded with more than 20 passengers. “The worst scenario was 38 pupils and 25 adults crammed into two Toyota Quantums. “We also found, 13 pupils in a Toyota Avanza, 18 pupils loaded on the back of an Isuzu bakkie, 11 in a Ford EcoSport and 11 in a Nissan Livina,” he said. “We will continue with the operation to ensure compliance with the Road Traffic Act.”